						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the Nṛisiṁhasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1553 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is damaged. It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1474, Paridhāvin, Pushya ba. 15,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1553 A.D., January 14, Saturday, (solar eclipse).</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land by Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Rāmarāju Kōnēṭi China-Tirumaladēva-mahārāju for the merit of his father.</p>						

						</summary>
